Veronica! Guess who just got
his own radio show?

616
00:30:25,375 --> 00:30:26,300
Me.

617
00:30:26,796 --> 00:30:29,372
I do feel like you had
something to do with it, though...

618
00:30:29,585 --> 00:30:32,373
You know, you helping
the boss's boyfriend.

619
00:30:33,108 --> 00:30:34,701
Well, it's a good thing
you got the show

620
00:30:34,765 --> 00:30:37,572
because I'm about
to make Trish real unhappy.

621
00:30:38,048 --> 00:30:40,743
Trish, did you talk to Kurt yet?

622
00:30:40,808 --> 00:30:41,823
No, what's up?

623
00:30:48,768 --> 00:30:50,872
My boyfriend has
a weight-lifting class,

624
00:30:51,136 --> 00:30:53,360
and I was meeting him
by the stadium, and I saw Kurt.

625
00:30:53,986 --> 00:30:55,511
I think he turned himself in.

626
00:30:55,965 --> 00:30:56,710
What makes you think...

627
00:30:56,817 --> 00:30:58,340
Coach Fry had him running the stadium,

628
00:30:58,867 --> 00:31:01,232
yelling like a maniac
about him losing the playbook

629
00:31:01,306 --> 00:31:04,901
and how he's gonna be running
the stadium steps every day.

630
00:31:04,986 --> 00:31:07,940
You were right, Trish.
That guy really has it in for Kurt.

631
00:31:07,997 --> 00:31:10,121
But he didn't get kicked off?

632
00:31:10,378 --> 00:31:13,490
I'd say getting kicked off
would have been a bargain.

633
00:31:17,057 --> 00:31:19,271
30 minutes...
That should be about right...

634
00:31:19,368 --> 00:31:21,820
30 minutes for Trish
to come apart at the seams.

635
00:31:25,266 --> 00:31:26,970
What is she doing in there?

636
00:31:31,847 --> 00:31:33,333
Redecorating?

637
00:31:39,168 --> 00:31:40,383
I took Kurt's playbook.

638
00:31:40,515 --> 00:31:41,591
You don't say.

639
00:31:42,355 --> 00:31:44,201
And now it's gone,
and if I don't find it,

640
00:31:44,265 --> 00:31:45,632
Kurt is gonna keep getting tortured.

641
00:31:45,797 --> 00:31:48,802
Well, the good news is
I lied about that.

642
00:31:49,258 --> 00:31:51,821
You wanted your boyfriend
to lose his scholarship

643
00:31:51,867 --> 00:31:55,002
just so, what, you two could spend
more time together?

644
00:31:55,067 --> 00:31:56,301
No.

645
00:31:56,845 --> 00:31:58,912
I wanted him off so he
wouldn't be miserable.

646
00:31:59,495 --> 00:32:02,220
That coach treats him
like a piece of meat.

647
00:32:03,268 --> 00:32:06,861
Kurt... Kurt absolutely lived
for that team.

648
00:32:07,078 --> 00:32:09,341
And when he wrecked his knee for them,

649
00:32:09,467 --> 00:32:10,351
how did they thank him?

650
00:32:10,436 --> 00:32:12,132
They made his life hell.

651
00:32:12,345 --> 00:32:15,452
Trish, you can't quit for him.

652
00:32:16,308 --> 00:32:17,873
We need to get that book back.

653
00:32:18,007 --> 00:32:21,802
Fine. But it's gone,
and I have no idea where it could be.

654
00:32:27,787 --> 00:32:30,950
Think about it. We know who has it.

655
00:32:40,327 --> 00:32:41,453
Where's the playbook, Larry?

656
00:32:42,708 --> 00:32:44,783
Get off me, you dumb goon!

657
00:32:44,946 --> 00:32:46,800
Where's the playbook, Larry?
Where's the playbook?

658
00:32:46,867 --> 00:32:48,363
